The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Bride stolen

 Ballia, Dec. 18: A groom had his bride stolen from under his nose by his brother in an Uttar Pradesh village, police sources here said. Before the marriage ceremony at Bishambhara village in Ballia could begin, the grooms brother raised a ruckus saying he wanted to marry the bride. Villagers then held a vote to decide which of the two men would marry her. The younger sibling won 32 votes out of 50.




